Zen Chat — OPTIONAL advanced overrides.

You do NOT need this file for a normal deployment. `docker compose up -d` runs
with sensible defaults: the backend auto-generates and persists its own secrets
and connects to the bundled Postgres/Redis. Create a root `.env` (next to
docker-compose.yml) only if you want to override something below.

Secrets note: JWT_SECRET and Z_CHAT_ENCRYPTION_KEY are auto-generated on
first boot and stored in the `secrets` volume. Set them here ONLY if you want
to pin specific values — and once data has been encrypted, never change
Z_CHAT_ENCRYPTION_KEY or stored WhatsApp tokens become unreadable.

── Infrastructure overrides ────────────────────────────────────────────
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=z-chat           # bundled Postgres password (also in DATABASE_URL via compose)
HTTP_PORT=8080                     # host port for the web UI
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:z-chat@z-chat-db:5432/postgres
REDIS_URL=redis://redis:6379
JWT_SECRET=                        # auto-generated if unset (openssl rand -hex 32)
Z_CHAT_ENCRYPTION_KEY=             # auto-generated if unset (different from JWT_SECRET)
CORS_ORIGIN=https://chat.axxeler.in,http://chat.axxeler.in
── Optional headless admin seed ────────────────────────────────────────
If both are set AND no users exist yet, the admin is created on boot and the
setup wizard is skipped. Otherwise you create the admin in the browser.
ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@example.com
ADMIN_PASSWORD=1234

── Meta WhatsApp Cloud API ─────────────────────────────────────────────
WhatsApp accounts are connected in the UI (Settings → WhatsApp). These are
optional extras: an app secret to verify inbound webhook signatures, and the
Graph API version.
META_APP_SECRET=8209c682297d1da66fbfa492350a85ee
META_API_VERSION=v21.0

── LLM provider fallbacks (AI Agents) ──────────────────────────────────
Each agent can bring its own key in the UI; these are global fallbacks.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
OPENAI_API_KEY=

── Google OAuth (Sheets) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
No env vars needed. An admin configures the Google OAuth Client ID, Client
Secret, and Redirect URI in the app under Settings → Integrations → Google;
they are stored encrypted in the database (coexistence.google_oauth_credentials).

── Other optional tuning (defaults shown) ──────────────────────────────
MEDIA_TRANSCODE_AUDIO=true         # ffmpeg Ogg→MP3 fallback for Safari
SEND_RATE_MAX=60                   # outbound messages per SEND_RATE_DURATION_MS
SEND_RATE_DURATION_MS=1000
TEMPLATE_SYNC_INTERVAL_MS=600000

FB_APP_ID=1503616021040143
FB_APP_SECRET=f89cca15a0126325cad51034886eaa10
FB_LOGIN_CONFIG_ID=1332325998505554